description: Sunrise host Natalie Barr has boldly asked on-air whether the missing submersible lost near the wreck of the Titanic should of ventured into the depths in the first place.

title: Mother shares photo of her immobilised baby girl who is squeezed into a glass tube for her X-ray
description: The hilarious video shows six-month-old Stevie, who is from Canada, with her arms up high in a glass tube, known as a Pigg-O-Stat, with her mother laughing in the background.

title: NHS plans to offer cancer tests to every ex-smoker in order to boost cancer survival rates
description: A pilot scheme found that three-quarters of lung cancer cases at stage one or two can be spotted by these checks. The free lung screening is said to be part of a number of initiatives planned.

title: Ferrari 458 worth $600,000 seized by police in Sydney, NSW, over $5.5million cryptocurrency scam
description: Two men have been charged following sweeping raids across Sydney as part of a four-month investigation into an  alleged $5.5million cryptocurrency scam.

title: Jetstar pilot Greg Lynn accused of murder of  campers in Victoria's Wonnangatta Valley cash problem
description: Ex-Jetstar pilot Greg Lynn accused of the murders of secret lover campers Russell Hill, 74, and Carol Clay, 73, is running out of cash to fund his defence.

title: Rep. Ocasio-Cortez will BOYCOTT Prime Minister Modi's speech to Congress
description: Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez will not attend India Prime Minister Narendra Modi's address to a joint session of Congress on Thursday out of protest of his record on human rights abuses.

title: Domain house prices report: sydney melbourne prices tipped to soar
description: Property market group Domain is forecasting a surge in house price even though the Reserve Bank is hiking interest rates at the most aggressive pace since 1989. High immigration is why.

title: Submersible pilot's wife is descendant of famous Titanic couple who died arm in arm
description: Wendy Rush is the wife of Stockton Rush, the CEO of OceanGate. He is among the five people on board the missing Titanic tourist sub. Her great-great-grandparents died in the 1912 disaster.

title: Explorers Club president says life-saving drones for Titanic sub search caught up in red tape
description: Richard Garriott, president of the Explorers Club, said on Wednesday that deep sea exploration company Magellan had not been able to send its underwater drones to the scene.

title: Racist transgender woman is found guilty of battering Chinese man on NYC subway
description: A man who assaulted an Asian man on the subway last year was found guilty of committing a hate crime in court on Wednesday.

title: French husband accused of 'drugging his wife and recording at least 51 men raping her'
description: Dominique allegedly invited his so-called guests into their home to rape his wife. It is understood that he would record the assaults and keep the footage on a USB drive in a file called 'ABUSES'.

title: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: Mortgage agony that could sink the Tories
description: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: When he promised in January to halve galloping inflation by the end of this year, Rishi Sunak seemed to be shooting at an open goal.

title: Powerball Australia: How Lotto wins have destroyed people
description: Winning the lottery isn't just seen as the answer to most Australians' money worries, it's become a metaphor for the best luck imaginable in life.

title: E-scooter riders who injure pedestrians could face two years in jail
description: Judges and magistrates have been told by the Sentencing Council that they should use section 35 of the Offences Against the Person Act of 1861 to prosecute e-scooter riders.

title: Horny tortoise, 60, crossed three roads and a bridge in epic quest for love
description: As the proud owner of a tortoise, Cathryn Scott, of Selkirk, Scottish Borders, was used to her pet enjoying life in the slow lane. But Tommy the tortoise had other ideas.

title: Fashion world in shock as Scottish designer finds label on brink of administration
description: Christopher Kane - who rose from modest beginnings in a Lanarkshire village to become an award-winning designer - is on the verge of putting his company into administration.

title: Rescue teams waiting since MONDAY for approval from 'incompetent' US Coastguard to help with search
description: One firm which has a vehicle capable of reaching 20,000ft depths is said to have applied on  Monday to take part in efforts to find the sub, with approval allegedly delayed until today.
